article.headline: Lipscomb 65, Campbell 64
article.story: BUIES CREEK, N.C. (AP) -- Trey Williams led five Lipscomb players in double figures with 15 points as the Bison held on for 65-64 victory over Campbell on Saturday. Jason Hopkins and Michael Teller scored 11 points apiece, while Eddie Ard and Brian Fisk added 10 each for the Bison (12-8, 6-3 Atlantic Sun Conference), who held Campbell to a season-low 64 points. Fisk made the second of two free throws to give Lipscomb a 65-62 lead with 19 seconds left. Jonathan Rodriguez missed a lay-up but Gibson tipped it in with 1.7 seconds left but Campbell couldn't get ahead. Russ Gibson and Ruell Pringle lead Campbell (8-10, 3-5 ASC) with 12 points apiece. Ledell Eackles added 11 points, seven rebounds and three steals.
